Description:
PERIOD PRIZE WITH DUAL STREET ACCESS!
Positioned to perfection with the best of Collingwood and Fitzroy in easy reach, this Federation gem delivers a lifestyle of immediate quality and class along with value-adding options to further enhance and expand (STCA). Beyond its gorgeous facade, the home's inviting interior comprises two genuinely large bedrooms, bathroom and separate WC, open lounge/dining area enhanced by a light-filled kitchen with timber benchtops, dishwasher and ample cupboard space. Add to this two gas-coal fireplaces, alarm system, high ceilings, internal laundry facilities, plus a brick-paved rear courtyard complete with off-street parking space (remote-controlled rollerdoor to Little Wellington Street). Enviably located, it's walking distance to Smith Street's cool cafes and renowned restaurants, boutique shops and major supermarkets, as well as trams to the CBD.
Insights: 35 Otter Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Vogue, vast and versatile!
With its towering ceilings, penthouse proportions and abundance of natural light throughout, this top-floor townhouse presents an environment of instant style and future flair in Collingwood's renowned Foy & Gibson precinct. Retaining its distinctive industrial edge, the home's enormous open-plan design currently offers 2 extra-large bedrooms (both with robes) and contemporary-style bathroom, expansive living/dining area and well-appointed kitchen with dishwasher and stainless steel cooking appliances. Other features include hydronic heating, exposed beams and polished floorboards, European laundry, plus intercom/secure entry foyer and two parking spaces on title. Stroll to Smith Street cafes and restaurants, shops and supermarkets, Victoria Parade trams and Fitzroy Gardens.
Insights: 27/120 Cambridge Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
A Near New Collingwood Stunner
Smith & Co, with its heritage facade, is ideally located in hip and happening Collingwood. Be part of the action in this spacious near new two bedroom apartment with its flowing floor plan and abundance of natural light. Opening into a contemporary black and white custom kitchen with island bench, premium European stainless steel appliances, dishwasher, stone benches and super stylish storage, an expansive living zone beyond, accesses the full width covered entertainers terrace. Featuring two double bedrooms with BIRs, the master boasting a chic en-suite, with a further prestige bathroom offering designer tiling, large walk-in shower, quality fixtures and fittings and a recessed euro laundry. The apartment includes central heating and air-conditioning, double glazed floor to ceiling windows, timber floors and a neutral interior palette, with secure parking for one and an additional storage cage to make life even more convenient. The development includes communal gardens, rooftop entertaining terraces with BBQ and library/lounge. Close to a supermarket, shops, cafes, bars and restaurants, with easy access to public transport making the CBD commute a breeze, this beautiful property is ideal for busy urban professionals or as a smart investment option.
Insights: 215/132 Smith Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Two-level terrace with courtyard in an exciting locale
A city-fringe retreat set back from the street with entry via side laneway and rear ROW access, this unique 2 bedroom and study residence extends over 2 enticing levels to a large rear courtyard that's private, peaceful and full of possibilities. This distinctive terrace retains its heritage character both up and downstairs with towering ceilings and polished timber floors framing a series of bright, flexible spaces enhanced by deft contemporary touches, that with Commercial 1 zoning, suggest more to come. At the heart of the action near Smith & Brunswick Streets, Yarra parkland and train station, this Victorian home includes glorious north-facing main bedroom (or lounge) with marble OFP, living room, smart kitchen with stainless-steel appliances, stylish modern bathroom, laundry/powder room and loads of smart storage.

The Urban Dweller

Description:
Inner-city oasis of light and space
Wow! Absolutely one of a kind, this secluded second-floor Islington apartment sets itself apart with its oversized dimensions, delightful leafy outlook and abundance of natural light throughout. A world away from the bustle of Hoddle Street, the home's whisper-quiet interior boasts 2 spacious bedrooms (both with mirrored robes), stylish ensuite and main central bathroom, open-plan living/dining area leading out to a large undercover terrace. Add to this a well-appointed kitchen with dishwasher and stainless steel cooking appliances, split-system heating and cooling (2 units), Euro laundry, plus lift to secure foyer, lower-level car space and enormous storage cage (3.8m x 3.5m). Stroll to Victoria Parade trams and North Richmond Station, cool cafes, renowned restaurants and Fitzroy Gardens.

Description:
"MINNIE VILLE"
With its iconic Victorian elegance, versatile design and quality enhancements, this balconied terrace delivers an outstanding inner-city lifestyle with close proximity to the best of Collingwood and Fitzroy. Instant appeal with scope to further enhance, the home's pristine interior comprises 3 bedrooms (extra-large master with balcony access) and contemporary bathroom, wide central lounge enhanced by an updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and ample cupboard space. Add to this gas heating, high ornate ceilings and polished timber floors, plus a sunny north-facing back garden with extensive paving and secure off-street parking via ROW. Easy access to a range of attractions including Smith Street cafes and trams, renowned restaurants and shopping precincts, Victoria Park Station.

Description:
Low-Maintenance, Inner-City Living At Its Best
Enjoying a quiet position at the centre of the highly regarded Islington Apartment building, this low-maintenance first-floor apartment boasts an exceptionally large north-facing terrace that floods the immaculately presented interior with natural light. An excellent opportunity for first home buyers or astute investors to secure a slice of the increasingly popular inner-north, the home comprises a well-appointed kitchen (stainless steel appliances, ample storage) that services the expansive open plan living and dining room opening onto the north facing balcony, gleaming central bathroom with Euro laundry, double bedroom with BIRs, reverse-cycle heating and air-conditioning, intercom entry with lift access and secure basement OSP on title with access via Islington Street. Located in a position offering the best in inner-city living, the apartment is central to an abundance of public transport options, all the backstreet cafes, bars and boutiques Collingwood is known for, vibrant Victoria Street restaurants and just a leisurely stroll through Fitzroy Gardens to Melbourne's hallowed MCG and the CBD.

Description:
Refurbished 2 Bedroom Plus Courtyard Plus Garage
It’s rare we can offer a first floor spacious and light filled refurbished two bedroom apartment with two big pluses – an L-shaped courtyard under licence from the O.C. and a lock up garage.
So whilst the apartment is incredibly attractive with its entry hall, modernised kitchen with meals area, two genuine double bedrooms with robes, an expansive lounge with a neutral décor, new carpets and a northerly aspect, those two pluses make this a must see for an owner occupier or astute investor.
Positioned at the rear of the block, away from any traffic noise yet within the hub of inner city life, a stroll to the delights of Smith and Johnston Streets, corner pubs and cafes and Yarra trail. Make time to have a look, you won’t regret the decision.

Description:
"New York On Oxford"
Enrich your inner-city living experience with this two/three bedroom warehouse apartment in the Foy & Gibson precinct, one of Melbourne's earliest industrial icons. Rich heritage beginnings are combined with thoroughly modern class in a position that places the best of the area's cosmopolitan culture at the doorstep. Soaring ceilings, exposed brick and expansive original windows create a brilliant New York feel through sweeping open plan spaces that feature an impressive entertainers' kitchen with central island servery. Above, a mezzanine level offers flexibility as an additional living domain or third bedroom with extensive storage, whilst two principle bedrooms (deluxe size main) both with BIRs and ensuites accompany a fitted study and powder room. Includes intercom entry, lift and secure parking.
Insights: 6/115 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 18 other 3 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
7 Star Sustainability 1 bedroom Apartment in Oxford & Peel
It is with much regret that we offer for sale our beautiful East-facing apartment on the second floor of the almost-new Oxford & Peel apartment building (just 50 apartments in the building).
Designed by Small Giants & Jackson Clements Burrows, this apartment building was built with sustainability at its core. The building is a socially progressive urban residential precinct with a 7 star sustainability rating and is only one year old. Superb location, in inner-city Collingwood, just one block from Smith St with it's cafes and restaurants and 2 blocks from Victoria St. Fantastic public transport options on both of these major corridors.
East facing apartment is a spacious 51sqm on the inside with a 5sqm balcony, with an industrial style. The apartment has: one bedroom, one bathroom, small desk area, dining area, combined living/kitchen, an outdoor balcony, laundry, 1 carpark, bike spaces and an extra lockable storage cupboard. The apartment building is fully secured, with caged parking spaces, security doors and intercom.
It has Engineered oak floorboards throughout with polished concrete in the bedroom and a tiled area outside. The high ceilings, and large glass panels make the apartment feel even more spacious and bright. The wooden/ply kitchen, has ample storage space, almost brand new kitchen (Miele oven and gas cooktop) and water filter (all just one year old).
A new smaller building has just being completed directly adjacent to the apartment. Honestly, it has blocked some view, but to our surprise it has blocked none of the light that fills the apartment, has provided wonderful privacy we didn't have before and we now know that no taller building is allowed to be built nearby so the present private but light-filled experience is ensured.
There is also a communal rooftop which you have full use of, that has a BBQ, tables, and incredible panoramic views of the city and all the way to the mountains over Abbotsford. There is wifi already connected throughout the whole building. It has a lift and downstairs in the building is a great café!
The apartment has no air conditioning but it has a 7 star thermal rating, is double glazed, cross ventilated and has ceiling fans for summer cooling and excellent hydronic heating for winter. All function fantastically.
This apartment is great as a home or investment. It currently rents out at an 80% occupancy rate through Airbnb, easily earning enough income to cover all mortgage/rates/bills plus extra to spare. Regretful sale but we need the equity for other ventures.
Looking for a quick sale with settlement at the end of September/beginning of October. Price is firm and fair, contract of sale is ready and we are ready to sell to the first person to accept our offer of sale. Let's show that an apartment can still be sold in an honest way, without all the real estate games.
Please phone us to organise an inspection or to receive a copy of the contract of sale.
Insights: 49 other 1 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Architectural excellence with space and light - Approx 64sqm
This superbly appointed apartment in the boutique 'Haus' development designed by acclaimed Stoll Long Architecture offers light-filled living on the East Melbourne border, close to Gertrude Street galleries, Smith and Brunswick Street cafes and the MCG. A highly functional floor plan comprises a spacious living/dining room with fitted study alcove, flowing to a covered balcony with an easterly aspect, one double bedroom with built-in robes, custom kitchen featuring stone benchtops, soft-close cabinetry, pull-out pantry and premium appliances, plus an elegant tiled bathroom/European laundry. This superior CBD-edge residence features engineered oak floors, double glazing, split-system air-conditioning throughout and ample storage, plus secure lift, video intercom and basement parking/storage.

Description:
Amazing space! Gothic Revival meets Neo- modernist design
***INSPECTIONS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY, PLEASE CONTACT AGENT TO PRE-REGISTER***
EXPRESSION OF INTEREST (UNLESS SOLD PRIOR) - CLOSES 11TH AUGUST 5PM
'The Courtyard House': This breathtaking inner-urban sanctuary, designed by owner-architect Ilana Kister, is the inner city's finest residence. Shortlisted in the INDE awards and 2017 Houses awards and featured in the current issue of Habitus, this light-flooded family home flowing to serene courtyards cited on 720sq.m. (approx.), a 17m solar heated/self-dosing lap pool and a spectacular roof garden is linked to the former St Saviour's church, now a gloriously versatile space for large-scale entertaining and home office use. Distinguished by curvilinear timber walls, waxed concrete floors and superior appointments, this unique home constructed on passive energy principles incorporates superbly scaled living and dining areas, 4 double bedrooms (dressing room and ensuite to main), state-of-the-art Miele kitchen and adjoining butler's kitchen, study, luxurious family bathroom, powder room and fitted laundry. Including a 4-car garage and additional parking space, 'The Courtyard House', bordering East Melbourne and close to leading restaurants and cafes, features home automation/Ethernet throughout, hydronic slab heating and air conditioning, custom storage, full security access control and double glazing.
Insights: 6 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 3 other 4 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.
